import spark.implicits._

import org.apache.spark.sql._
import org.apache.spark.sql.types._

// Definir clase (se usa `` para PriceSQFt por tener espacios)
case class Hogares(mls:Long,
                location: String,
                price: Double,
                bedrooms: Int,
                bathrooms: Int,
                size: Double,
                `price SQ Ft`: Double,
                status: String)

// Creacion de esquema
val miEsquema = new StructType()
                    .add("MLS", LongType, true)
                    .add("Location", StringType, true)
                    .add("Price", DoubleType,true)
                    .add("Bedrooms", IntegerType,true)
                    .add("Bathrooms", IntegerType,true)
                    .add("Size", DoubleType, true)
                    .add("Price SQ Ft", DoubleType, true)
                    .add("Status", StringType, true)
